Former @wvuhoops stud John Flowers now works as a financial analyst, but said he’d still give Jon Elmore buckets…Elmore said that would never happen. Tune in at 7 pm/et on ESPN+ to find out!

Thank you to Mrs. Diana Jackson for inviting me to celebrate being recognized as the SBA West Virginia District Office Legacy Business Recipient. Thanks for being a mentor and inspiration as I transition from basketball to the business world. You are the blueprint 💪🏾

The dream was to make it the NBA. I didn’t make it to the moon, but I was still amongst those stars. What a ride. 12 years. 7 different countries. 3 different continents 🌎Got to experience different people and cultures. Made lots of new friends.. some who I now consider family. Learned how to speak different languages. 3 championships🏆Lots ….of partying 🕺🏾lol some great coaches.. some terrible coaches. Ate croissants on the Eiffel Tower 🇫🇷 Went drifting in Tokyo 🗼Went to Oktoberfest in Germany 🍺 At tacos at a Pyramid in Mexico City 🌮Lived in Buenos Aires. Cheered, sang songs, and burned flares with soccer fans in Uruguay ⚽️Witnessed my people in Caracas riot everyday against the government 🔫..and took cold showers for 6 months🥶 lol and plenty more.

It wasn’t all sunsets and rainbows. A lot of blood sweat and tears went into this. Hours in the gym perfecting my craft. Still dealt with the politics. BAD COACHES. Waiting to get signed some years. Having to prove myself every single year. Being away from family. Missing bdays and holidays. It was definitely a grind.. but a grind well worth it. 

Overall, it was a great experience. I Just want to say thank you to God for allowing me to experience and see more in 12 years than most people see in a life time. Basketball gave me the opportunity to play a game for a living. Basketball took me to places that I never dreamed of going.  I could have played 5 more years but I couldn’t imagine leaving my family every year. Yea I coulda brought em… maybe I should have .. but I feel there’s a bigger calling. 
Been ballin my whole life… I’m a financial advisor now …time to see what the future holds. 

Thank you Basketball

Had a great dinner with some top Analyst from Capital Group. Mihir Mehta who is an equity investment Analyst with research reaponsibility for U.S. semiconductor and hardware companies.
Also Sandro Lazzarini who is a fixed income investment analyst with research responsibilities for technology and financial companies. 
Very informative dinner about what’s going on in our markets. The key to being a successful financial advisor is to never stop educating myself. Thank you guys for coming to WV! Hope you enjoyed the scenery.

Glad I had the opportyity to talk with and teach my lil bros about some of the the basics of investing their money. 
In this new era where players are allowed to make so much money, it’s cruicial that they understand the strategy and different investments that they can use. And Who better to learn it from than someone who’s actully been in their shoes. 
Athletes have a small window to make life changing money. Be smart with it. I’m glad I was able to pay it forward to my brothers from my Alma mater, and teach them some of the things I’ve learned as a financial advisor and through my 12 years of playing basketball as a pro.
